Coming this Sunday at 5pm, a NEW one-off feature length Walt Disney World vlog 🥳

Last month I flew to Orlando to attend a convention for work. But I couldn't exactly go all the way to Orlando without at least bringing you a bit of Disney magic 😉. So, I booked myself into a short stay at my Disney Vacation Club home resort: Disney's Riviera Resort. 🇫🇷🎨🇮🇹

Just as I was passing through the airport though, I found out a tropical storm was likely to become a hurricane and would fall exactly on my Disney stay 🤦🏻‍♂️. 

However, I was determined to make the most of an unexpected situation 😊. I figured it would still be worth vlogging the experience to show you what it's like to be in a Disney resort during a tropical storm/hurricane. Whilst also giving you a comprehensive tour of my home resort, sharing some festive fun and bringing you some bonus content this holiday season. 🎄

Thankfully the storm was kind to Orlando and the parks were able to open up on a delayed schedule. With that, I was able to vlog a bit of Epcot and attend Mickey's Very Merry Christmas Party with the ever so lovely @cheersears_ family.

Set your reminders now to make sure you don't miss out on the live premiere this Sunday at 5pm GMT (12pm EST). See you then! ✨

Walking in a winter wonderland ❄️

📷: @oohgaryc (and yes we are vlogging 😉)

For those of you that may need it today: someone's reel, post, story or carousel of their 2022 highlights, are just that; the highlights. I know I'm one for seeing these posts on social media and instantly comparing myself to them. However, I think it's worth remembering, these are not the whole picture.

Take this picture for example. On the face of it, you might see a happy-go-lucky Disney fan in the most magical place on earth, having the best day ever. Whilst some of that's true, what this picture, or the vlog of this day doesn't show, was an uphill mental health struggle. It doesn't show my breakdown on a bench in International Gateway, the long moments of silence as I internalised my biggest vulnerabilities and that without @oohgaryc's friendship and support, I'd of had a hard time coming back from what my inner demons were telling me that day.

Sure I could post a fun recap of all the Disney trips I was lucky enough to enjoy this year. But the truth is, this year has been one of the most difficult for me personally. At the start of this year, I really wasn't sure I'd find my way back to the person I once was, and there was one low point where I genuinely considered scrapping everything: including vlogging (I'm not, don't worry).

Lucky for me, I found my way back. It wasn't easy, but I enrolled myself in therapy, made some big changes to my business, built in more self-care and was open with my friends and family about what I was struggling with. The road forward for me, was built brick by brick. One small step at a time.

So, whilst you're seeing people's 2022 wrapped posts, try to remember, that's not the whole picture. Try not to compare yourself to someone else's highlights, as there's almost always low points we sometimes choose to forget.

If you're struggling at the moment, I promise you; you are not alone. A next step might be asking for help. For me, there was no way I would've made it to where I am today, without loving, patient and kind support. 

Whatever your 2023 holds, I hope it brings you inner peace, self-content, joy and healing ❤️ Happy New Year lovelies ✨

Additionally, stock may be limited and/or some products sold out. As such, we strongly recommend shopping during the Early Christmas Orders period to avoid missing out.

As always, orders are processed on a first come, first served basis. International shipping is available at checkout. Due to the handmade nature of the candles, once they're sold out, I'm afraid that's all the stock we have for the remainder of the year. If we can ship orders early, we of course will. However, please keep the mid-November estimated dispatch in mind when placing your order.

In any case, Happy (early) Holidays! And I hope you're able to get everything on your Christmas list 🎁🎄🎅🏼
My audition to stand in for Tinkerbell during Happily Ever After ✨

I'm a big Halloween Horror Nights fan, and this trip I took the opportunity to do the Unmasking the Horror Tour for the first time! 🎃

This backstage tour allows you to see some of the houses with the lights on, learn some behind the scenes information and nerd out over all the Easter Eggs and hidden details.

This wasn't gifted or sponsored, but I've created a whole review of the experience on my stories (on my Universal highlights). This covers the price, experience, my review and more. 

Shoutout to my awesome tour guide PJ, who was so knowledgeable, funny and his love of HHN was infectious. It's a ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️+ from me! I've left now wanting to work for HHN making these houses, the creative team have such a cool job (and they're very very good at what they do). Hats off to the cast, crew and creative of #HHN32, this year was awesome!

My house rankings are as follows:

1. Universal Monsters Unmasked
2. Dr. Oddfellows 
3. Blood Moon
4. The Last of Us
5. Yeti Campground Kills 
6. Stranger Things
7. The Darkest Deal
8. The Exorcist 
9. Duelling Dragons
10. Chucky (this one was triggering for me).

@universalorlando @horrornights #hhn32 #halloweenhorrornights

4,570 days ago, I set up my YouTube channel 🤩 It's been one heck of a ride so far, and I'm so grateful for @youtube giving me a space to be my authentic and Disney obsessed self! I've been lucky enough to have some of you lovely people along for the ride ❤️ and the opportunity to turn my hobby into a career. 🤯

Last week my friend Brogan and I attended an event organised by the @ytcreators UK team! I felt a lot of 'imposter syndrome' being there, but it turned out to be a lot of fun! It was so nice to catch up with one of my favourite people in one of my favourite places in the UK 🥰

Here's to the next 4,570+ days ✨ Thank you to YouTube, my fellow creator friends (mostly @oohgaryc 😉) and those of you that have subscribed, for helping make my channel what it is today. 🥹
